Born as '''Daniel Alberto Laiseca''' he is a software developer from Buenos Aires, Argentina and is the founder of [[Syntheway]] Virtual Musical Instruments company and author of [[Magnus Choir]] music software.

He also has developed software synthesizers and samplers like the [[Master Hammond B3]] organ, [[Syntheway Strings]], [[Harmodion]], [[Realistic Virtual Piano]], Virtual Sitar, [[Organux]], [[Aeternus Brass]], RetroMagix Harpsichord, ElectriKeys Electric Piano, Percussion Kit and DAL Flute among others.


